## Scenario 4 — Hazmat Release on Public Roadway (transport accident)
##
## DOT is primary (public roadway + transport). EPA fires for release
## above RQ. USCG fires if near navigable waters. OSHA HAZWOPER
## applies ONLY for emergency responders at the scene — OSHA does NOT
## regulate the driving activity itself.
##
## Key distinction from Scenario 1: no loading-dock → different
## OSHA applicability (response only vs. facility HCS). Framework set
## is DOT + EPA + USCG (not DOT + EPA + OSHA as at the dock).
##
## Baseline triples extracted from ehs-ontology-v3.2.ttl (line 1255).

PREFIX ehs: <http://example.org/ehs-ontology#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

ASK {
    ehs:Scenario_ChemSpill_Roadway rdf:type ehs:ContextualComplianceActivation ;
        ehs:triggeredByType       ehs:ChemicalHazard ;
        ehs:hasActionContext      ehs:TransportAction ;
        ehs:hasContextCondition   ehs:PublicRoadway ,
                                  ehs:FullRelease ,
                                  ehs:AboveReportableQuantity ;
        ehs:activatesFramework    ehs:DOT_Framework ,
                                  ehs:EPA_Framework ,
                                  ehs:USCG_Framework .
}
